\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Program Design and Authority
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall design the security awareness and role-based training curriculum.
 Human Resources shall administer the general security awareness program for County personnel.
 The Assistant IT Director shall develop and deliver the technical and role-based training content.
 The training program implements the workforce-competency requirements established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Workforce Roles,
 Responsibilities,
 and Competency Framework) and the data-handling obligations established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Data Governance and Classification Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Training Cadence
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Initial Training
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall complete initial security awareness training prior to receipt of access.
 Initial training is paired with the user acknowledgment required under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Acceptable Use of Information Technology Resources Policy).
 The IT Director shall not authorize provisioning of access under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Access Control Policy) until both initial training completion and acceptable use acknowledgment execution are verified.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Annual Refresher
\series default
:
 All County Personnel shall complete annual refresher training at a maximum cadence of twelve (12) calendar months from the date of the most recent completion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Event Retraining
\series default
:
 Personnel involved in a security event shall complete remedial training within thirty (30) calendar days of the event,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AT-2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Account Suspension Trigger
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall suspend the account of any user who fails to complete the annual refresher within the prescribed cadence,
 or who fails to complete assigned remedial training within thirty (30) calendar days,
 in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Literacy Content
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The general security awareness curriculum shall address,
 at minimum,
 the following topics:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Insider Threat
\series default
:
 Recognition of indicators of malicious or accidental insider threat.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Social Engineering
\series default
:
 Identification of phishing,
 vishing,
 and related deception techniques.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Data Handling
\series default
:
 Protection of Criminal Justice Information (CJI),
 Personally Identifiable Information (PII),
 and other classified data in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Role-Based Training
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Personnel in roles with elevated privileges or specialized data-handling obligations shall complete role-based training in addition to the general literacy program,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AT-3 (Role-Based Training).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Privileged Users
\series default
:
 Personnel holding privileged accounts (Tier L3 and above as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
) shall complete role-based training addressing administrative responsibilities,
 privileged credential handling,
 and audit accountability.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Privacy-Data Handlers
\series default
:
 Personnel handling Criminal Justice Information (CJI),
 Personally Identifiable Information (PII),
 or Protected Health Information (PHI) shall complete role-based privacy training addressing the obligations defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Privacy and Data Protection Policy) and the data classification handling requirements defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Physical Access Holders
\series default
:
 Personnel with unescorted access to physically secure locations as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Physical Security and Environmental Controls Policy) shall complete role-based training addressing visitor management,
 tailgating prevention,
 physical incident reporting,
 and protection of Criminal Justice Information (CJI) from unauthorized observation or access.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Practical Exercises
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall conduct not fewer than two (2) spear-phishing simulations annually.
 The Assistant IT Director shall assign remedial training within thirty (30) calendar days to personnel who fail a simulation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Records Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Information Operations shall retain training-completion records and signed acknowledgments in accordance with LRDA 20071725 (IT Employee Access Control and Security Awareness Files) and CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section AT-4 (Training Records) for a minimum of three (3) calendar years from the end of the calendar year in which the record was modified or the employee's access rights were terminated.
 Each training record shall identify,
 at minimum,
 the individual,
 the assigned role or access classification,
 the training title,
 the completion date,
 the delivery method,
 the result,
 the remediation status where applicable,
 and the record custodian.
\end_layout

